About : 
=========
WhaTV is a simple information diffusion system, aimed to be used either in web
browsers or embedded in entreprise diffusion systems.


Changelog
=========

0.0.1 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Initial release.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.2 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Iframe and video full support with proper css.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.3 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Adding Flash support.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.4 (2010-10-18)
----------------
Adding modular Ambimage support.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.5 (2010-10-19)
----------------
Get rid of majority of jquery calls,
Ambilight support,
Adding an options system to specify image and video options (not fully implemented)
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

Roadmap :
=========
0.0.6 : Option system with (fullscreen, ambimage/ambilight, original, crop) options
0.1.0 : First stable release with proper "finished loading" event firing, animated header, footer with date and quick messages.
0.2.0 : Widgets support
0.2.1 : Proof of concept : meteo widget
0.3.0 : Modular transition system with some examples
0.4.0 : Powerpoint support

Later : node.js authentication and synchronization system
Image has to be vertically centered.
Slide isolation : a failed slide won't prevent other to show correctly
Photo album
Could it be possible to have x #content, where x is the number of slides?
Replace $.getJSON by $.get & JSON.parse
Vertical centering
CSS3 image animation support (examples : http://developer.apple.com/safaridemos/showcase/transitions/) 
Module system, where we specify urls of extensions files.